+# CareOn primitives convergence — decision document
+
+**Status:** Analysis / decision input — **read-only**. No code, components, imports, inventory statuses, or tests changed. No migration performed.
+**Date:** 2026-06-18
+**Subject:** `CareCommandPrimitives` (A, `client/src/components/care/CareCommandPrimitives.tsx`) vs `CareDesignPrimitives` (B, barrel: `CareDesignPrimitives.tsx` + re-exports from `CareUnifiedPage.tsx`, `CareSurface.tsx`, `CarePageScaffold.tsx`, `CareAppFrame.tsx`, `CaseStatusBadge.tsx`).
+**Companion:** governance status in `CAREON_COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md` (A = `Needs consolidation`, Review/Merge — unchanged by this document).
+
+---
+
+## 0. Headline findings (correct the earlier assumption)
+
+- **A is actively used, not an orphan:** 21 production pages import it; ~19 use its worklist grid, ~17 its metric strip/card. A supplies the **page shell, worklist grid, interactive KPI-filter card, and pagination** that pages actually render.
+- **B is the quality target:** token-strict (no raw hex/rgba), a11y-instrumented (`role=status/alert`, focus rings), and **test+story covered**; A has **zero tests/stories** and notable hardcoded styling (`bg-white`, an inline `rgba` shadow, `yellow-300/400` row tones, raw `text-[NNpx]` sizes).
+- **No export name is shared** between A and B — every overlap is *functional*, not nominal. This means the two can coexist during migration with **no naming collisions**, and a guard can later forbid A without ambiguity.
+- **The barrel's queue/metric exports are underused** because pages get those from A instead — so B's `CareWorkRow`/queue/metric primitives are the intended-but-not-yet-adopted equivalents.
+
+**Recommended canonical direction:** converge on **B (`CareDesignPrimitives`)**, but only after B *absorbs* A's genuinely-needed capabilities that B currently lacks (interactive metric-as-filter card, metric strip, optionally real pagination, a shell convenience). Then migrate the 21 consumers A→B in phases, and only then tighten A's status to `Deprecated` → `Forbidden`.
+
