+## 2. Unique functionality (must be resolved before deprecating A)
+
+**Only in A (B must gain or pages must change):**
+- Interactive **`CareMetricCard`** as a filter toggle (`onClick`, `aria-pressed`, tonal states) — B only has the passive `CareMetricBadge`.
+- **`CareMetricStrip`** metric-grid wrapper — no B equivalent.
+- **`CareWorklistPagination`** — A-only (and non-functional today).
+- **`CareWorklistRowAction`** overlay-click wrapper — folded into B's `CareWorkRow` but the generic pattern is A-only.
+- Generic **slot-driven row** (`CareWorklistRow` + caller `cols`) vs B's opinionated named-prop row.
+
+**Only in B (already canonical, A has nothing):** states, alerts, sections, badges, flow/match primitives, app scaffold/header with metric slot, `CareInfoPopover`, `CareOperationalSelect`, `PrimaryActionButton`, `CARE_RHYTHM`.
+
+**Same-name-different-implementation:** none.
+**Safely mergeable (A → existing B):** shell, worklist row/body/header/card, toolbar/tabs/filterpanel, row-action.
+**Must-keep (capability) but currently A-only:** interactive metric card, metric strip; pagination only if a real need is confirmed.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Recommended canonical primitives (per category)
+
+- App shell/header → **`CarePageScaffold` + `CareUnifiedHeader`/`PageHeader`** (B).
+- Operational queue → **`CareWorkRow` + `CareOperationalQueueHeader` + `CarePrimaryList` + `CareWorkListCard`** (B), using `OPERATIONAL_QUEUE_GRID_*`.
+- Filters/search/tabs → **`CareSearchFiltersBar` + `CareFilterTabGroup/Button`** (B).
+- KPI → **a new token-strict, tested interactive `CareMetricCard` + `CareMetricStrip` promoted into B** (absorbing A's capability; de-hardcode font sizes).
+- States/alerts/badges/sections/flow → **B** (unchanged).
+- Pagination → **product decision** (implement in B or drop).
+
+---
+
+## 4. Product / design decisions — FORMALLY RECORDED (2026-06-18)
+
+Direction: `CareDesignPrimitives` (B) is the target architecture; `CareCommandPrimitives` (A) stays `Needs consolidation`; no consumer migration yet.
+
+### D1 — Canonical row model
+`CareWorkRow` (B) **remains the canonical operational row.** A generic slot-/grid-row variant may be added **only when all** of the following hold: (a) multiple pages demonstrably need the same pattern; (b) the pattern does not reasonably fit the existing named props; (c) the variant is centrally tested and documented. **Free per-page grid composition is not an allowed standard.**
+
+### D2 — Interactive metric cards
+**`Metric-card-as-filter` is an Approved interaction pattern.** Interactive and passive metrics stay **separate**: an interactive `CareMetricCard` for filter/toggle behaviour; a passive metric/KPI component (`CareMetricBadge`/`CareKPICard`) for information only. The interactive variant must have, at minimum: `aria-pressed`; a clear selected state; keyboard operability; a focus state; token-strict styling; tests and stories.
+
+### D3 — Pagination
+**No canonical pagination primitive is added now.** Pagination is built only when a real, active use case exists, defined by: dataset size; page state; a backend- or client-side contract; a UX choice; and testable navigation. A's current **decorative** pagination is **not** adopted as a capability.
+
+### D4 — Migration parity
+**Mandatory:** behavioural parity; information parity; accessibility parity; responsive parity.
+**Not mandatory:** pixel-perfect parity where the target design system deliberately introduces better token, spacing, focus, or theming consistency. (Visual-regression baselines are updated with design sign-off, not treated as regressions.)
+
