+## 5. Phased migration proposal (small, reversible; no migration in this document)
+
+- **M0 — Absorb A's unique capabilities into B** (token-strict, tested): interactive `CareMetricCard`, `CareMetricStrip`, (optional) `CarePagination`. No page changes yet. *Exit: B exports cover every A export that has consumers; B tests/stories updated.*
+- **M1 — Shell-only consumers** (lowest risk, 2 files): `PlacementPage`, `AccessDeniedPage` (import only `CareCommandShell`) → B scaffold+header. *Exit: pages render; Playwright shell smoke green.*
+- **M2 — Filter/metric-only consumers** (~6 files): `RapportagesPage`, `DocumentenPage`, `ZorgaanbiedersPage`, `AudittrailPage`, `RegiosPage`, `settings/InstellingenSettingsExperience`, `ProviderProfilePage` → `CareSearchFiltersBar` + B metric card/strip. *Exit: per-page visual diff approved.*
+- **M3 — Full worklist consumers** (~12 files, highest risk): `PlacementTrackingPage`, `ActiesPage`, `MatchingQueuePage`, `WorkloadPage`, `SignalenPage`, `IntakeListPage`, `AanbiederreactiePage`, `SystemAwarenessPage`, `AssessmentQueuePage`, `AanbiederPortaalPage`, `GemeentenPage`, `GebruikersPage` → migrate worklist grid to `CareWorkRow`/queue primitives, **one page per PR**, each with visual-regression + golden-path smoke. *Exit: all pages migrated; A importers = 0.*
+- **M4 — Tighten status:** set A `Deprecated` in the inventory (the PR-D forbidden-import guard then blocks new imports) → after a soak period, `Forbidden` / delete `CareCommandPrimitives.tsx`. *Exit: see §7.*
+
+Migration order within each phase = ascending by number of A exports used (fewest first), so blast radius grows gradually.
