+## 6. Risks
+
+- **No safety net on A's side:** A has zero tests/stories. Migration correctness rests on B's tests + Playwright visual regression + per-page smoke — these must exist/pass before M3.
+- **Broad active surface:** 21 consumers, ~19 on the worklist grid → layout-regression risk if `CareWorkRow`'s opinionated props don't cover every page's columns (drives decision §4.1).
+- **Visual shift:** A's `bg-white`/`yellow`/raw sizes vs B's tokens → light/dark appearance will change; needs design sign-off + baselines.
+- **Behaviour shift:** A's `CareMetricCard` is interactive; a naive swap to B's passive badge would silently drop filtering — M0 must preserve the interaction.
+- **Coordination with backend work:** keep migration PRs separate from the `views.py` decomposition to avoid entangled reviews.
+
+---
+
+## 7. Exit criteria before any component status is tightened (Deprecated/Forbidden)
+
+A's governance status may move from `Needs consolidation` → `Deprecated` only when **all** hold:
+1. B has token-strict, **tested** equivalents for every A export that currently has consumers (incl. interactive metric card + strip + chosen row model + any required pagination).
+2. The canonical row-model and KPI-pattern **product/design decisions (§4) are recorded** (in `DECISIONS.md` / `CAREON_DESIGN_SYSTEM_V1.md`).
+3. **All 21 consumers migrated** off A — verified by the PR-D forbidden-import guard reporting zero importers (or an explicit grep).
+4. Playwright **golden-path + visual-regression green** across migrated pages; design sign-off on visual parity.
+
+Move `Deprecated` → `Forbidden` (or delete the file) only after a soak period with the guard active and no new imports. This document performs **no migration and changes no status**; it is decision input only.
